description: From Medieval Latin abrenunciare, from Latin ab- (“from”) + renuntio (“revoke”).

verbs.description: abrenounce (third-person singular simple present abrenounces, present participle abrenouncing, simple past and past participle abrenounced)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To renounce; to contradict. [Attested from the mid 16th century until the mid 17th century.]
examples: They abrenounce and cast them off.
